"CLOSURE PROGRAM
"Vars set/overwritten in this app: Оё,Y,R,Str1,B,T,C,X,Z (N & Str1 used by CLOSUREI)
"Other vars also used by SVTOOLS, called from this program


ClrHome

"INITIAL SETUP OF LISTS, VARS AND SETTINGS
"-----------------------------------------
100.01в†’Оё:prgmSVTOOLS

"---- Main Menu ----
Lbl A
Menu("Closure Calc","Start new",N,"Redo last",R,"Save last rslt",SL,"Arbtrary datum",AD,"Help",H,"Quit",X

"---- Redo last ----
Lbl R
ClrHome
"Print existing values
100.05в†’Оё
prgmSVTOOLS
ClrHome
Goto C

"--------- Closure Input ---------
Lbl N
100.3в†’Оё
0в†’Z
prgmSVTOOLS

"--------- Closure Calculation ----------
Lbl C
100.1в†’Оё
{1}в†’вЊЉPARAM
prgmSVTOOLS
0в†’Оё

ClrHome
Disp "Survey Closure"
Disp "--------------"
Disp "B, B+180, D:"
Disp BпЂ”DMS
Disp B+(B<180)180-(Bв‰Ґ180)180пЂ”DMS
Disp round(D,3),D

"---------- Optional Closure Rotation -------------
"Provide a hidden option to rotate the answer by
"pressing +,-, or -
"OVERWRITES: Y,R,Str1,B

"How many iterations before we timeout? (Very roughly, seconds x 55)
90*55в†’R

"We need to store 0 in Ans before beginning loop
0

"Pause here until a key is pressed, or timeout is reached
Repeat Ans or R=0
::R-1в†’R
::getKeyв†’Y
End

If Y=95 or Y=85 or Y=104:Then
::"Var for remembering the rotation
::1в†’dim(вЊЉROTAT
::вЊЉROTAT(1)в†’R
::"Ask for rotation amount
::"     ----------------
::Disp "Rotate answer by
::Disp "how much? D.MMSS
::Disp ". to reuse prev:
::Disp RпЂ”DMS
::Input "> ",Str1
::If Str1в‰ ".":Then
::::expr(Str1)в†’R
::::"Parse DMS format to decimal
::::iPart(R)+iPart(fPart(R)*100)/60+fPart(R*100)*100/3600в†’R
::::Rв†’вЊЉROTAT(1)
::End
::B+Rв†’B
::B+360(B<0)-360(B>360)в†’B
::Disp "Rotated closure:
::Disp "B, B+180, D:"
::Disp BпЂ”DMS
::Disp B+(B<180)180-(Bв‰Ґ180)180пЂ”DMS
::Disp round(D,3)
::If Dв‰ round(D,3):Disp D
::Pause 
End

"-------- Display Double (& Quad) Missing Dist Result -------
"This section does NOT apply the rotation above. Does it need to?
"Not really... since we already know bearings, and only looking for dists. OK to leave as is.
If T:Then
::ClrHome
::
::"Quad missing dist
::If T=3:Then
::::Disp "Missing dist #1:","(V,W)"
::::Disp Lв‚ѓ(dim(Lв‚ѓ)-3)пЂ”DMS
::::Disp round(V,3)
::::Disp Lв‚ѓ(dim(Lв‚ѓ)-2)пЂ”DMS
::::Disp round(W,3)
::::Pause 
::::ClrHome
::::Disp "Missing dist #2:"
::Else
::::Disp "Missing dists:"
::End
::
::Disp "(X,Z)"
::Disp Lв‚ѓ(dim(Lв‚ѓ)-1)пЂ”DMS
::Disp round(X,3)
::Disp Lв‚ѓ(dim(Lв‚ѓ))пЂ”DMS
::Disp round(Z,3)

::"DMD calc complete
::"Cleanup by removing final bearing if only 1 was initially provided,
::"So that it's returned to the state when user began the program.
::If T=1 or T=3:dim(Lв‚Ѓ)-1в†’dim(Lв‚Ѓ

::Pause 
End

Goto X

"================= Save closure ====================
"READS FROM: B,D,X,Z
"OVERWRITES: T,C
"AVOID USING: F,I,L
Lbl SL
"Save last closure to L1 and L2
dim(Lв‚Ѓ)-dim(Lв‚‚)в†’T
If T=0:Then

::"Convert bearing from dec to short DMS format
::iPart(B)+iPart(fPart(B)*60)/100+fPart(B*60)/60*3600/10000в†’C
::Cв†’Lв‚Ѓ(dim(Lв‚Ѓ)+1)
::Dв†’Lв‚‚(dim(Lв‚‚)+1)

::"Display result
::Disp "Saving to list:",BпЂ”DMS,C,D

End

"Saving double missing dists
If T=2:Then
::Disp "Saving dists:",X,Z
::Xв†’Lв‚‚(dim(Lв‚‚)+1)
::Zв†’Lв‚‚(dim(Lв‚‚)+1)
End

Return



"=================== Arb Datum Calc ===================
"Uses vars: вЊЉARB1,вЊЉARB2,Str1,C,G,H,вЊЉKNOWN,X
"Overwrites: Lв‚Ѓ,Lв‚‚

Lbl AD
"     ----------------
Disp "You're at point
Disp "X.
Disp "Measure
Disp "X-A and X-B
Disp "using any
Disp "starting
Disp "bearing.

"Declare array in case it doesn't exist yet
2в†’dim(вЊЉARB1
2в†’dim(вЊЉARB2

"Recall entries in case user wants to reuse them
"ARB1 = arb bearings X-A and X-B (D.MMSS)
"ARB2 = arb distances X-A and X-B
вЊЉARB1в†’Lв‚Ѓ
вЊЉARB2в†’Lв‚‚

"Reset L3
"100.01-->Оё
"prgmSVTOOLS

Pause 

"Note: This section doesn't support multiple hops.
"      Only used for sighting to 2 points directly.
"      If you need to place >1 unknown point between
"      2 known points, then you need to do manually.

Disp ". to reuse last
Disp "
Input "X-A Bear: ",Str1
If Str1=".":Then
::"Display prev values
::100.05в†’Оё:prgmSVTOOLS
Else
::{expr(Str1)}в†’Lв‚Ѓ
::Input "X-A Dist: ",C
::{C}в†’Lв‚‚
::Input "X-B Bear: ",C
::Cв†’Lв‚Ѓ(2)
::Input "X-B Dist: ",C
::Cв†’Lв‚‚(2)
End

Disp "","Calculating...

"Remember X-A and X-B entries for later reuse
Lв‚Ѓв†’вЊЉARB1
Lв‚‚в†’вЊЉARB2

"Find A-B (via closure B-X-A)
"First swap the two and 
"reverse the distance to B
{Lв‚Ѓ(2),Lв‚Ѓ(1)}в†’Lв‚Ѓ
{В­Lв‚‚(2),Lв‚‚(1)}в†’Lв‚‚

"Calculate the closure
100.1в†’Оё
{1}в†’вЊЉPARAM
prgmSVTOOLS

"Display the closure result
ClrHome
Disp "Arbitrary
Disp "closure A-B:
Disp BпЂ”DMS
Disp round(D,3),D
Pause 

"Remember result for later use (G and H)
Bв†’G
Dв†’H

Disp "
Disp "On next screen
Disp "enter known
Disp "traverse(s) from
Disp "A to B.
Pause 

"Declare array in case it doesn't exist yet
2в†’dim(вЊЉKNOWN)

"POPULATE L2 and L3 TO SUPPORT RECALLING OF PREV ENTRIES USING .
"TODO: Support recalling multiple traverses here! Does not currently.
{вЊЉKNOWN(1)}в†’Lв‚ѓ
{вЊЉKNOWN(2)}в†’Lв‚‚

"Ask for closure input. Recalling will redisplay LKNOWN values.
100.3в†’Оё:0в†’Z:prgmSVTOOLS

"N=1 signifies that we're reusing prev values. Do nothing except reset L3.
If N=1:Then
::100.01в†’Оё:prgmSVTOOLS
End

"If only a single bear+dist, save to lKNOWN
If N=2:Then
::"If a negative dist, we'll flip the bearing
::{fPart((Lв‚ѓ(1)+180(Lв‚‚(1)<0))/360)*360,abs(Lв‚‚(1))}в†’вЊЉKNOWN
End

"Otherwise if multiple traverses, calc the closure:
If N>2:Then
::Disp "","Calculating...
:"Calc closure of A-B
::100.1в†’Оё
::{1}в†’вЊЉPARAM
::prgmSVTOOLS
::"Closure gives us B-A, so we'll flip 180 to get A-B
::{B+(Bв‰¤180)180-(B>180)180,D}в†’вЊЉKNOWN
::ClrHome
::Disp "A-B bear+dist:
::Disp вЊЉKNOWN(1)пЂ”DMS,BпЂ”DMS,round(D,3)
::If round(D,3)в‰ D:Disp D
::Pause 
End

ClrHome
"     ----------------

"Calc necessary rotation
вЊЉKNOWN(1)-Gв†’X
"Calc distance diff (including a mod(360), keeping a result from -180 to 180)
fPart(X/360)*360-(X>180)360+(X<В­180)360в†’X

"Display diff of bearing and distance
"ClrHome
Disp "Diff:
Disp XпЂ”DMS
Disp вЊЉKNOWN(2)-H

"Warn when distance is high
If abs(вЊЉKNOWN(2)-H)>0.006:Then
::Disp "","Dist is high.","Continue?
::Pause "
::ClrHome
End

"Reload LARB1 and LARB2 into main lists
вЊЉARB1в†’Lв‚Ѓ
вЊЉARB2в†’Lв‚‚

Disp "Corrected X-A:
Disp fPart((Lв‚ѓ(1)+X+360)/360)*360пЂ”DMS
Disp fPart((Lв‚ѓ(1)+X+360+180)/360)*360пЂ”DMS
Disp round(Lв‚‚(1),3)
"Disp Lв‚‚(1)

Pause 

Disp "Corrected X-B:
Disp fPart((Lв‚ѓ(2)+X+360)/360)*360пЂ”DMS
Disp fPart((Lв‚ѓ(2)+X+360+180)/360)*360пЂ”DMS
Disp round(Lв‚‚(2),3)
"Disp Lв‚‚(2)

Pause 
Return



